{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Typically, ReAct (Yao et al., 2023) uses an iterative process where a LLM generates thoughts and actions based on current observations until task completion.",
    "Reflexion (Shinn et al., 2023) introduces a self-reflection mechanism to improve reasoning quality.",
    "Meanwhile, ADAPT (Prasad et al., 2023) employs a recursive strategy that breaks down tasks into subtasks and allows further decomposition when necessary.",
    "We extend these capabilities further by introducing a multi-agent framework where the task is dynamically decomposed and each subtask is then assigned to specially generated subagent.",
    "This approach allows for more flexible and efficient task management, especially in complex and unpredictable scenarios."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Typically, ReAct (Yao et al., 2023) uses an iterative process where a LLM generates thoughts and actions based on current observations until task completion.",
